Description: Modern asteroid detection software for citizen science
 AstroFind is asteroid detection software for citizen science and
 educational use. Compatible with the IASC / MPC workflow.
 Outputs ADES 2022 format (XML and PSV) for submission to the MPC.
 .
 Features: FITS viewer (SER/XISF/TIFF/PNG), plate solving via
 astrometry.net and ASTAP, star detection (SEP), aperture photometry,
 blink comparison, Moving Object Detection across ≥3 images,
 calibration (dark/flat/bias), and full bilingual EN/PT-BR interface.
 .
 NOTE: This is a beta release. All features are implemented but
 end-to-end validation with real telescope FITS files has not yet
 been performed.
